3. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks): The paper discusses the performance of the proposed blind channel estimation method in different types of channels, which can be related to social and information networks. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia): The paper discusses the use of time-frequency resources in massive MIMO downlink transmission, which can be related to multimedia applications. 
5. cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper proposes a method for channel estimation, which can be related to machine learning techniques.
